WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.160
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.080
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.390 --> 00:01:45.920
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:55.220
Hiriluk's Cherry Blossoms

24
00:01:55.220 --> 00:01:56.010
Hey, Nami!

25
00:01:56.720 --> 00:01:59.680
Are you sure you're okay?

26
00:02:00.810 --> 00:02:02.640
I'm fine! I'm feeling great!

27
00:02:02.640 --> 00:02:07.770
Hey, let's go say bye
to doctor granny and acorn pops, too.

28
00:02:03.230 --> 00:02:06.440
Done! In commemoration of our arrival,

29
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:08.650
I present Snow Queen V!

30
00:02:07.770 --> 00:02:09.140
Don't be silly.

31
00:02:08.650 --> 00:02:11.360
Hey! How dare you kick
Snow Queen V!

32
00:02:09.140 --> 00:02:11.360
Give him and Doctorine some privacy.

33
00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:12.950
Mind your manners!

34
00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:14.570
He's lived alone with her for six years.

35
00:02:14.570 --> 00:02:17.330
I'm sure it'll be a tearful farewell.

36
00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:22.830
Doctorine may act tough,
but she's actually a big softie.

37
00:02:23.540 --> 00:02:24.830
Really?

38
00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:28.340
So, we're really leaving
without a word, huh?

39
00:02:28.340 --> 00:02:29.590
That's right.

40
00:02:29.590 --> 00:02:34.050
Once Chopper's back, we'll descend
the mountain and sail to Alabasta pronto!

41
00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:36.510
Does that sound good to you, Vivi?

42
00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:39.260
Yeah, if a doctor comes with us–

43
00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:39.970
A doctor?

44
00:02:39.970 --> 00:02:43.180
Okay then, I'll get the ropeway ready.

45
00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:45.440
Hey, Luffy! Give me a hand.

46
00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:47.650
Whoa, there's a ropeway?!

47
00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:50.780
That's awesome!

48
00:03:00.370 --> 00:03:01.490
Oh?

49
00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:04.000
It seems there are
some patients missing.

50
00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:05.830
They escaped...

51
00:03:06.460 --> 00:03:09.290
disobeying your orders...

52
00:03:09.710 --> 00:03:12.300
I see... What troublesome brats.

53
00:03:22.310 --> 00:03:23.770
Doctorine!

54
00:03:25.350 --> 00:03:26.940
Doctorine!

55
00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:30.520
I need to talk to you!

56
00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:33.900
Chopper, where have you been?

57
00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:37.160
Go downstairs and help them
set up the cannons.

58
00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:40.410
Listen, Doctorine!
I'm gonna be a pirate.

59
00:03:40.410 --> 00:03:41.990
I'm going with them!

60
00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:43.660
What?!

61
00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:45.250
I'm going out to sea!

62
00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:49.420
I'm going to be their ship's doctor
and travel around the world!

63
00:03:49.420 --> 00:03:51.290
Don't be absurd!

64
00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.090
Listen here. You're my
one and only assistant!

65
00:03:56.090 --> 00:03:59.010
Who do you think
taught you medicine?!

66
00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:02.470
Are you really that ungrateful?!

67
00:04:02.470 --> 00:04:04.770
Th-That's not it...!

68
00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:06.930
I really appreciate you, Doctorine,

69
00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:11.270
and I will always love this country
where I met you and Doctor!

70
00:04:12.440 --> 00:04:14.440
Then stay here.

71
00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:19.200
You'll never get another chance
to live in a lavish castle like this.

72
00:04:19.660 --> 00:04:21.780
Pirates are deadbeats.

73
00:04:21.780 --> 00:04:24.580
You'll wind up dead in no time.

74
00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:26.200
I'm fine with that!

75
00:04:27.330 --> 00:04:29.290
Don't get cocky!

76
00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:32.920
Who's ever heard of
a reindeer going out to sea?!

77
00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:34.590
That's right! I am a reindeer!

78
00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:35.380
But...

79
00:04:35.380 --> 00:04:36.340
I'm also a man!

80
00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:44.430
You sure talk big...

81
00:04:44.430 --> 00:04:46.770
In any case, I won't allow it.

82
00:04:46.770 --> 00:04:50.440
If you want to leave that bad,
you'll have to go through me!

83
00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:52.610
Doctorine...

84
00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:59.900
A crybaby like you, a man?!

85
00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:02.410
Don't make me laugh!

86
00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:04.660
Doctorine...

87
00:05:04.660 --> 00:05:06.370
But they...

88
00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:07.330
Shut up!

89
00:05:07.330 --> 00:05:09.960
Let's go!

90
00:05:11.330 --> 00:05:12.420
...understand.

91
00:05:12.420 --> 00:05:13.630
Shut up!

92
00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:17.760
I won't let you have your way!

93
00:05:26.140 --> 00:05:29.350
Get back here, Chopper!

94
00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:32.940
Wait!

95
00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:36.520
What's all that commotion?

96
00:05:36.520 --> 00:05:38.650
Well, whatever it is,

97
00:05:38.650 --> 00:05:42.030
we'd better get these 
cannons outside the castle

98
00:05:42.030 --> 00:05:45.160
or Dr. Kureha will skewer us!

99
00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:46.580
Don't be silly!

100
00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:48.240
Wait!

101
00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:50.710
I won't let you get away!

102
00:05:50.710 --> 00:05:53.290
Chopper!

103
00:05:53.290 --> 00:05:55.040
Get back here!

104
00:05:56.540 --> 00:05:59.260
What's all that racket?
It's coming from the castle.

105
00:05:59.260 --> 00:06:01.420
Come on. Have some courtesy...

106
00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:05.720
Can't they keep it down while 
others are saying goodbye?

107
00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:11.430
I'm sorry, Doctorine,
but I want to see the world!

108
00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:20.570
What does someone like you
hope to accomplish at sea?

109
00:06:20.940 --> 00:06:24.030
Are you going to live in
a fantasy like that quack did?

110
00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:27.030
You're wrong!

111
00:06:27.030 --> 00:06:28.660
It wasn't a fantasy!

112
00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:32.460
Doctor's research was completed!

113
00:06:32.830 --> 00:06:34.330
Hey, he's coming–

114
00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:36.670
What?!

115
00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:38.130
What's going on?!

116
00:06:38.130 --> 00:06:39.880
He's being chased!

117
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:41.510
Hey!

118
00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:43.420
The ropeway is rea–

119
00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:46.140
Everyone, hop on the sleigh!

120
00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.140
I'll take you down the mountain!

121
00:06:51.930 --> 00:06:53.680
– What?!
– What?!

122
00:07:00.780 --> 00:07:02.150
Hey, look over there!

123
00:07:02.150 --> 00:07:03.950
What the heck is that?

124
00:07:06.030 --> 00:07:07.490
That's the witch's sleigh!

125
00:07:59.330 --> 00:08:01.000
What was that?!

126
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:03.090
It was Dr. Kureha's reindeer!

127
00:08:03.090 --> 00:08:05.300
And those pirates were on the sleigh!

128
00:08:05.300 --> 00:08:07.170
What happened up there?!

129
00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.590
What happened to Wapol?

130
00:08:08.590 --> 00:08:10.680
Is Dalton okay?!

131
00:08:14.680 --> 00:08:18.310
That was fun! Let's do it again!

132
00:08:18.310 --> 00:08:20.150
We're setting sail now, you moron!

133
00:08:20.150 --> 00:08:22.020
I-I thought I was a goner...

134
00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:24.190
Huh? Where am I?!

135
00:08:24.190 --> 00:08:27.650
Oh, Sanji! You're awake?

136
00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:34.990
Is it really okay to leave it at that?

137
00:08:38.210 --> 00:08:43.090
The pet I was fostering is finally
being adopted. That's all.

138
00:08:45.420 --> 00:08:48.420
I'm not a fan... of sappy goodbyes!

139
00:08:55.060 --> 00:08:56.310
Come on!

140
00:08:55.430 --> 00:08:56.310
Ow!

141
00:08:56.310 --> 00:08:59.850
Let's prepare a send-off to remember!

142
00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:01.150
Ouch...

143
00:09:03.440 --> 00:09:05.730
I finally did it... This is it!

144
00:09:05.730 --> 00:09:09.110
This reaction...
I've waited thirty years for this.

145
00:09:09.570 --> 00:09:12.740
Doctor! It wasn't
just a fantasy, right?!

146
00:09:12.740 --> 00:09:15.990
Your research was completed, right?!

147
00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:19.540
Or was that a lie, too?

148
00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:21.290
I did it, Chopper!

149
00:09:21.290 --> 00:09:23.500
I've completed my research!

150
00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:27.510
You must've known I'd be crushed
if you died without succeeding!

151
00:09:27.510 --> 00:09:30.260
"Nothing's impossible when a man
raises a skull and crossbones flag!"

152
00:09:30.260 --> 00:09:32.470
I wish I could hear you
say it again, Doctor!

153
00:09:37.140 --> 00:09:39.430
Are you ready, young men?!

154
00:09:39.430 --> 00:09:40.480
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

155
00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:41.810
Fire!

156
00:09:42.650 --> 00:09:45.310
Listen, Kureha. This dust...

157
00:09:50.030 --> 00:09:52.280
Dr. Kureha! What in the world–

158
00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:53.860
Just shut up and watch.

159
00:09:59.370 --> 00:10:01.160
It's coming from the castle!

160
00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:03.420
Huh? Is Wapol shooting off fireworks?

161
00:10:03.420 --> 00:10:05.130
Idiot! That's cannon fire!

162
00:10:05.130 --> 00:10:06.380
What's going on?!

163
00:10:06.380 --> 00:10:07.590
Take cover!

164
00:10:07.590 --> 00:10:10.630
Dammit! It's too dark to see anything!

165
00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:13.380
Dr. Kureha, we've fired all the ammo!

166
00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:14.930
Light 'em up!

167
00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:27.770
Amazing...!

168
00:10:27.770 --> 00:10:28.860
Yeah...

169
00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:31.360
It's beautiful...!

170
00:10:33.320 --> 00:10:37.530
This is the answer I found
after thirty long years!

171
00:10:37.530 --> 00:10:41.200
This truly is a fantastic sight!

172
00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:45.500
I'll never understand what went on
in that old quack's head.

173
00:10:46.130 --> 00:10:48.500
I will make cherry blossoms bloom!

174
00:10:48.500 --> 00:10:52.460
Once my invention is complete,
this country will be saved!

175
00:10:53.920 --> 00:10:55.550
Get out of here, quack!

176
00:10:55.550 --> 00:10:58.930
Dammit! I thought
lizard eyeballs would work!

177
00:11:00.890 --> 00:11:04.980
Listen up. This red dust is special.

178
00:11:04.980 --> 00:11:09.770
It will bond to
the white snow in the air...

179
00:11:10.150 --> 00:11:13.240
and make vivid pink snow fall!

180
00:11:19.660 --> 00:11:21.040
Doctor!

181
00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:23.830
Doctorine!

182
00:11:58.490 --> 00:12:01.030
I'm not going to shoot you!

183
00:12:01.030 --> 00:12:03.330
My name is Dr. Hiriluk!

184
00:12:03.330 --> 00:12:04.450
I'm a doctor!

185
00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:06.830
Tony Tony Chopper.

186
00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:10.420
That's a cool name, isn't it?
That's what I'll call you.

187
00:12:10.750 --> 00:12:13.920
Chopper... you'll make a fine doctor!

188
00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:15.420
I'm living proof of that.

189
00:12:21.890 --> 00:12:25.140
Even if I disappear,
my dream will come true.

190
00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:27.850
What a marvelous life it's been!

191
00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:34.280
Thank you, Chopper.

192
00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:45.040
Now...

193
00:12:45.540 --> 00:12:47.250
have a safe trip,

194
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:48.660
my foolish son...!

195
00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:01.180
This day is the best!

196
00:13:01.180 --> 00:13:03.720
The moon's out with
cherry blossoms in bloom.

197
00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:05.560
Chopper! Hey, Chopper!

198
00:13:05.560 --> 00:13:06.560
You rascal!

199
00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:08.890
How long are you gonna
sit there in a daze?

200
00:13:09.850 --> 00:13:11.350
Drink!

201
00:13:10.350 --> 00:13:11.350
What?

202
00:13:11.350 --> 00:13:13.650
Bust out a song!

203
00:13:12.630 --> 00:13:13.650
What?

204
00:13:13.650 --> 00:13:15.940
Here, stick these chopsticks
up your nose!

205
00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:16.820
What?

206
00:13:16.820 --> 00:13:19.190
Man, what a great view
of the cherry blossoms!

207
00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:22.740
How could we not party
at a time like this?!

208
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.410
Are you surprised?

209
00:13:24.410 --> 00:13:28.120
You sure picked some
crazy friends, you know!

210
00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:30.870
Friends...?

211
00:13:30.870 --> 00:13:32.000
Yup.

212
00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:35.130
They can be a lot to handle,
but now that you're one of us,

213
00:13:35.130 --> 00:13:36.840
you'll have to get used to it.

214
00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:42.680
Karoo! What were you
doing frozen in the river?

215
00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:48.600
He must've slipped or something!
He's such a klutz!

216
00:13:48.600 --> 00:13:50.770
Quiet, Mr. Bushido!

217
00:13:51.390 --> 00:13:53.020
Yeah...

218
00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:56.020
He said that Zoro guy went
swimming and disappeared.

219
00:13:56.020 --> 00:13:59.740
He thought Zoro was in trouble,
so he jumped in to help and got frozen.

220
00:13:59.740 --> 00:14:01.820
So it was your fault!

221
00:14:01.820 --> 00:14:02.570
Ow...

222
00:14:02.570 --> 00:14:05.870
Tony, you can understand
what Karoo is saying?

223
00:14:05.870 --> 00:14:10.370
Yes. I can communicate
with animals because I am one.

224
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:12.210
You can talk with animals?

225
00:14:12.210 --> 00:14:14.210
That's incredible, Chopper!

226
00:14:14.210 --> 00:14:17.130
As if your medical expertise
wasn't enough...!

227
00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:19.000
Dummy!

228
00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:22.420
Complimenting me like that
won't make me happy, you jerk!

229
00:14:22.420 --> 00:14:23.760
– He sure looks happy.
– He sure looks happy.

230
00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:26.720
Nami, what do you mean
by medical expertise?

231
00:14:26.720 --> 00:14:28.970
Chopper is a doctor!

232
00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:33.440
Dr. Kureha herself trained him
to be a first-class physician!

233
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:34.940
– What?!
– What?!

234
00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:37.690
Chopper! You're a doctor?!

235
00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:38.940
Incredible!

236
00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:39.730
No way!

237
00:14:39.730 --> 00:14:41.110
Oh, come on!

238
00:14:41.110 --> 00:14:44.070
What did you think he was
when you asked him to join us?!

239
00:14:44.070 --> 00:14:46.620
A seven-point transforming reindeer.

240
00:14:47.070 --> 00:14:48.240
Emergency rations.

241
00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:49.030
What?!

242
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:55.290
Oh, no! I was in such a hurry
I forgot my medical supplies!

243
00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:57.500
Are you sure? Then, what's this?

244
00:14:56.920 --> 00:14:57.500
What?

245
00:14:58.500 --> 00:14:59.630
My bag!

246
00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:01.510
It was in the sleigh.

247
00:15:02.380 --> 00:15:03.590
How come...?

248
00:15:03.590 --> 00:15:05.010
How come?

249
00:15:05.010 --> 00:15:07.930
Didn't you prepare for
the trip by yourself?

250
00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:45.880
I guess she read you like a book,
even until the very end.

251
00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:50.510
She's a wonderful person.

252
00:15:50.350 --> 00:15:52.100
I got snot on the chopsticks!

253
00:15:51.430 --> 00:15:52.260
Yeah...

254
00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:53.140
You got this!

255
00:15:57.310 --> 00:16:00.190
Hey, Chopper! Give it a try!

256
00:16:00.190 --> 00:16:01.690
Seriously!

257
00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:02.690
What are you doing?!

258
00:16:01.690 --> 00:16:03.650
While you're reminiscing...

259
00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:05.530
Right, Chopper?

260
00:16:04.190 --> 00:16:06.200
Stop it, guys! Don't come here!

261
00:16:05.530 --> 00:16:06.780
Chopper...?

262
00:16:06.780 --> 00:16:08.410
Not you, too!

263
00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:12.910
Okay... guys!

264
00:16:12.910 --> 00:16:15.370
Attention!

265
00:16:15.370 --> 00:16:16.960
You bastard!

266
00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:20.250
Well, I'd like to introduce
our new crewmate to you,

267
00:16:20.250 --> 00:16:22.130
Sanji! Get him!
Tony Tony Chopper!

268
00:16:22.130 --> 00:16:25.260
He's gonna be our crew's doctor,
and to celebrate–

269
00:16:22.750 --> 00:16:24.550
I...

270
00:16:25.260 --> 00:16:26.470
Listen, you jerks!

271
00:16:26.470 --> 00:16:28.510
Quit it!

272
00:16:28.510 --> 00:16:30.510
It's fine, it's fine!

273
00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:30.510
I...

274
00:16:31.850 --> 00:16:33.720
Oh yeah?!

275
00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:35.930
Guys! Stop it!

276
00:16:35.930 --> 00:16:38.640
You wanna piece of me?!

277
00:16:36.480 --> 00:16:38.640
I've never had this much fun before.

278
00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:39.980
Yeah!

279
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:40.440
Another chopstick!

280
00:16:41.020 --> 00:16:43.980
Let's have a toast for our new friend!

281
00:16:43.980 --> 00:16:45.860
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

282
00:16:45.860 --> 00:16:50.990
– Cheers!
– Cheers!

283
00:16:53.780 --> 00:16:56.950
I wonder if they've left
the island by now.

284
00:16:56.950 --> 00:17:01.460
A reindeer with a first-rate heart
and first-rate skills as a doctor...

285
00:17:01.460 --> 00:17:06.710
If the cherry blossoms that Hiriluk put
his life into really did lead to a miracle...

286
00:17:08.380 --> 00:17:13.470
I guess it must be that clumsy
reindeer going out to sea.

287
00:17:13.470 --> 00:17:14.760
That kid...

288
00:17:15.260 --> 00:17:17.890
acting like he's all grown up...

289
00:17:18.310 --> 00:17:20.890
He'll be a fine ship's doctor.

290
00:17:21.730 --> 00:17:25.730
So, what are you going to do
from here on out?

291
00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:28.360
Before this...

292
00:17:28.740 --> 00:17:32.240
I was captain of Wapol's Royal Guard.

293
00:17:32.240 --> 00:17:35.410
I will have to atone for that sin.

294
00:17:35.870 --> 00:17:42.620
I've considered leaving and entrusting
this new country to its citizens.

295
00:17:42.620 --> 00:17:46.340
I see... Is that what you've decided?

296
00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:47.880
No...

297
00:17:47.880 --> 00:17:51.930
I've realized that running away
isn't the path to redemption.

298
00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:54.640
This land is breaking
the shackles of monarchy,

299
00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:57.890
and a new country made by
the citizens' hands is about to be born.

300
00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:03.900
Perhaps there's some way I can
contribute to its birth by remaining.

301
00:18:04.650 --> 00:18:10.440
I feel that is indeed a way
that I can begin to make amends.

302
00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:13.070
Young man...

303
00:18:13.070 --> 00:18:17.120
you truly do care for this country.

304
00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:20.830
Care for this country, you say...

305
00:18:21.790 --> 00:18:27.540
I once learned that lesson
from a mere ten-year-old girl.

306
00:18:26.590 --> 00:18:30.420
The Holy Land, Mary Geoise

307
00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:30.420
The World Conference?

308
00:18:30.420 --> 00:18:32.510
Such a worthless, tiresome affair.

309
00:18:32.510 --> 00:18:34.550
Indeed, my liege.

310
00:18:36.300 --> 00:18:40.220
I wonder if the Kingdom of Drum
can continue like this...

311
00:18:40.560 --> 00:18:43.600
The rift between its king
and citizens keeps growing...

312
00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:48.070
It's the ruler of Alabasta...

313
00:18:48.070 --> 00:18:50.610
King Nefertari Cobra!

314
00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:50.610
Nefertari Cobra
Ruler of Alabasta

315
00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:56.780
So that's the famously benevolent
and wise king of Alabasta.

316
00:18:58.370 --> 00:19:00.240
Dragon the Revolutionary...

317
00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:02.370
His ideology is dangerous.

318
00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:06.330
It's clear that in five or six years,

319
00:19:06.750 --> 00:19:11.800
this man will become capable
of threatening the World Government.

320
00:19:14.130 --> 00:19:15.630
Dumb hippos...

321
00:19:15.630 --> 00:19:18.260
This has nothing to do
with my country.

322
00:19:18.260 --> 00:19:22.640
My methods of governing give no room
for revolutionaries to mislead my people.

323
00:19:22.640 --> 00:19:25.190
If you all want to capture him,
do it on your own!

324
00:19:25.190 --> 00:19:26.520
Wapol!

325
00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:28.360
Cease your selfishness!

326
00:19:28.360 --> 00:19:31.070
Do you not realize
the Reverie's importance?!

327
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:33.900
Have some self-awareness!

328
00:19:34.570 --> 00:19:36.410
Damn you, Nefertari Cobra!

329
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:40.830
What an unpleasant
conference that was.

330
00:19:41.790 --> 00:19:42.660
That's...

331
00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:46.120
the daughter of that loathsome Cobra!

332
00:19:49.580 --> 00:19:51.670
Oops! My hand slipped!

333
00:19:51.670 --> 00:19:52.840
King Wapol!

334
00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:54.510
Princess Vivi!

335
00:19:54.510 --> 00:19:58.140
Oh, apologies! Aren't you
the princess of Alabasta?

336
00:19:58.140 --> 00:20:01.510
Poor child, being that
hopeless king's daughter!

337
00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:03.180
You knave! What are you doing?!

338
00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:05.310
Stop it, Igaram! I'm fine!

339
00:20:07.190 --> 00:20:09.940
I'm sorry, too, for bumping into you.

340
00:20:11.770 --> 00:20:13.980
What an extraordinary child...!

341
00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:19.780
When sovereigns gather for the Reverie,
even a minor argument can trigger a war.

342
00:20:19.780 --> 00:20:22.160
Knowing that,
she tolerated the slight...

343
00:20:23.750 --> 00:20:25.290
What a shrewd child!

344
00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.370
What a repulsive brat.

345
00:20:29.370 --> 00:20:30.880
Let's go, Dalton.

346
00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:32.380
Apologies.

347
00:20:36.210 --> 00:20:39.130
It hurts!

348
00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:43.760
You were magnificent, Princess Vivi.

349
00:20:43.850 --> 00:20:46.770
The princess' love for her country...

350
00:20:47.430 --> 00:20:49.440
her nobility...

351
00:20:49.440 --> 00:20:51.480
hasn't changed one bit.

352
00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:55.530
How splendid she turned out to be.

353
00:20:58.320 --> 00:20:59.740
Dalton...

354
00:21:00.740 --> 00:21:04.080
We also still care for this country.

355
00:21:04.080 --> 00:21:07.580
Let us help this land rise anew.

356
00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:16.050
Hiriluk...

357
00:21:16.050 --> 00:21:18.670
This country will surely be reborn...

358
00:21:18.670 --> 00:21:21.800
just like your son, Chopper!

359
00:21:21.800 --> 00:21:25.180
Dalton, bad news!

360
00:21:25.640 --> 00:21:28.310
I just remembered something terrible!

361
00:21:28.310 --> 00:21:29.270
What is it?

362
00:21:29.270 --> 00:21:31.020
Check this out.

363
00:21:32.480 --> 00:21:35.820
It's him! The straw hat pirate
who beat Wapol!

364
00:21:35.820 --> 00:21:37.440
There's no doubt about it!

365
00:21:37.820 --> 00:21:41.280
His bounty is 30 million belly?
Who are these people?

366
00:21:41.280 --> 00:21:42.570
Oh?

367
00:21:42.570 --> 00:21:45.030
Seems they weren't
just ordinary criminals.

368
00:21:45.990 --> 00:21:47.290
Where did you get this?

369
00:21:47.290 --> 00:21:50.960
Well... I completely forgot
to report it to you, but...

370
00:21:51.370 --> 00:21:52.870
about a week ago,

371
00:21:52.870 --> 00:21:57.880
a traveler suddenly appeared
in the town of Robelle.

372
00:21:59.210 --> 00:22:02.720
It was a strange day.
It didn't snow at all.

373
00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:05.100
We don't even know
where he made landfall.

374
00:22:05.100 --> 00:22:07.470
Anyway, he went on to say

375
00:22:07.470 --> 00:22:12.850
that he was after Blackbeard,
the pirate that attacked this country.

376
00:22:12.850 --> 00:22:16.190
But once he realized that Blackbeard
was long gone, he said,

377
00:22:16.190 --> 00:22:18.530
Then let me ask you
one more question.

378
00:22:18.530 --> 00:22:21.990
Has a pirate wearing
a straw hat come through here?

379
00:22:21.990 --> 00:22:25.990
When we said we didn't know,
he showed the wanted poster and said,

380
00:22:25.990 --> 00:22:28.740
If he shows up here...

381
00:22:30.330 --> 00:22:31.370
Shows up...?

382
00:22:31.750 --> 00:22:37.000
...tell him I'll be waiting in Alabasta,
but only for ten days.

383
00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:38.340
Got it?

384
00:22:40.590 --> 00:22:42.840
Hey! Hold on a second!

385
00:22:42.840 --> 00:22:44.340
What's your name?

386
00:22:44.340 --> 00:22:47.300
Oh, yeah. I forgot...

387
00:22:48.810 --> 00:22:50.470
My name is Ace.

388
00:22:50.470 --> 00:22:53.480
If you tell him that,
he'll know exactly who I am.

389
00:22:59.610 --> 00:23:01.360
Hey, grab that guy!

390
00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:03.320
He's trying to dine and dash!

391
00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:05.490
Just tell him, okay?!

392
00:23:08.450 --> 00:23:11.830
He'll wait in Alabasta
for ten days, huh?

393
00:23:14.160 --> 00:23:16.790
Dr. Kureha, what's the matter?

394
00:23:16.790 --> 00:23:18.290
You look out of it.

395
00:23:18.290 --> 00:23:21.920
Have you heard of Gol D. Roger?

396
00:23:21.920 --> 00:23:22.630
D.?

397
00:23:23.340 --> 00:23:24.930
You mean Gold Roger?

398
00:23:25.340 --> 00:23:28.180
Is that what he's called these days?

399
00:23:29.890 --> 00:23:31.810
It looks like...

400
00:23:32.270 --> 00:23:37.730
my reindeer left with one hell of a guy.

401
00:23:38.150 --> 00:23:40.020
So...

402
00:23:41.190 --> 00:23:44.110
the will of D... lives on!

403
00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:53.040
So, what's Alabasta?

404
00:23:53.040 --> 00:23:55.000
It's the country ruled by Vivi's father.

405
00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:59.170
A villain named Crocodile is trying
to take over Alabasta right now.

406
00:23:59.170 --> 00:24:02.500
I hear that Crocodile is one of
the Seven Warlords of the Sea.

407
00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:04.260
Seven Warlords of the Sea?

408
00:24:04.260 --> 00:24:07.510
A group of pirates sanctioned
by the World Government.

409
00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:09.800
Pirates sanctioned
by the government?

410
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:13.470
Yeah. They're overwhelmingly strong.

411
00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:21.190
They crush other pirates one by one,

412
00:24:21.190 --> 00:24:26.030
hence the government authorization.

413
00:24:26.530 --> 00:24:29.360
Crocodile, huh...?
I can't wait to meet him.

414
00:24:29.360 --> 00:24:31.930
Crocodile is a hero in Alabasta

415
00:24:31.930 --> 00:24:34.790
because he stops the pirates
who raid the towns.

416
00:24:34.790 --> 00:24:38.160
But that's just his public facade.

417
00:24:38.620 --> 00:24:42.910
He is the mastermind
behind the civil war

418
00:24:42.910 --> 00:24:44.880
engineered to take over Alabasta.

419
00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:47.630
No one has noticed it.

420
00:24:48.260 --> 00:24:50.590
Neither the citizens... nor my father...

421
00:24:50.590 --> 00:24:51.760
Alright then!

422
00:24:51.760 --> 00:24:55.020
I've just gotta kick this
Crocodile guy's butt, right?!

423
00:24:55.390 --> 00:24:56.270
Correct.

424
00:24:56.270 --> 00:25:00.810
If we can first stop the civil war
and expel Baroque Works...

425
00:25:00.810 --> 00:25:02.230
Baroque Works?

426
00:25:03.020 --> 00:25:05.900
That's right. You don't know
about them either, do you?

427
00:25:05.900 --> 00:25:08.650
To be honest, I'm a little lost myself.

428
00:25:08.650 --> 00:25:11.240
Baroque Works has
a complicated system.

429
00:25:11.740 --> 00:25:13.700
The system is actually quite simple.

430
00:25:14.080 --> 00:25:16.950
Starting at the top,
there's the boss, Crocodile...

431
00:25:16.950 --> 00:25:19.250
also known as Mr. 0.

432
00:25:20.460 --> 00:25:25.460
Taking orders directly from the boss
are twelve agents and one animal.

433
00:25:25.460 --> 00:25:29.630
Each of the top twelve men
is paired with a female agent.

434
00:25:31.180 --> 00:25:34.180
There's Mr. 1 and Miss Doublefinger.

435
00:25:34.680 --> 00:25:37.680
Mr. 2 doesn't have a partner, though.

436
00:25:38.020 --> 00:25:41.350
Mr. 3 is the candle man
we met in Little Garden, right?

437
00:25:41.350 --> 00:25:44.560
Yes. He was paired up
with Miss Golden Week.

438
00:25:44.560 --> 00:25:46.610
Oh, that girl.

439
00:25:47.150 --> 00:25:50.360
Mr. 4 is paired up with
Miss Merry Christmas.

440
00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:53.620
However, I don't have much
information on those two.

441
00:25:53.620 --> 00:25:54.820
And that snot guy!

442
00:25:54.820 --> 00:25:55.740
Mr. 5, right?

443
00:25:55.740 --> 00:25:56.450
Snot?

444
00:25:56.450 --> 00:25:58.200
Yeah, he used booger bombs.

445
00:25:58.200 --> 00:26:00.580
Mr. 5's entire body is a weapon.

446
00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:04.330
Miss Valentine has the powers
of the Kilo-Kilo Fruit.

447
00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:07.300
It's that woman who can
change her weight freely, right?

448
00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:11.840
Mr. 1 through Mr. 5
are called "officer agents."

449
00:26:11.840 --> 00:26:14.390
They all have devil fruit abilities,

450
00:26:14.390 --> 00:26:17.010
and they only take on
the most important missions.

451
00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:22.190
Mr. 6 through Mr. 13
oversee lower-level employees.

452
00:26:22.190 --> 00:26:26.400
They collect funds at
the start of the Grand Line.

453
00:26:26.400 --> 00:26:28.900
You know, there was
a strange monkey and chicken.

454
00:26:29.820 --> 00:26:32.740
They would be
Mr. 13 and Miss Friday.

455
00:26:32.740 --> 00:26:37.490
They are a punishment squad who primarily
deal with members who fail missions.

456
00:26:37.990 --> 00:26:42.620
Additionally, the officer agents'
200 underlings are called "billions,"

457
00:26:42.620 --> 00:26:46.380
and the frontier agents have
1,800 subordinates called "millions."

458
00:26:47.130 --> 00:26:50.210
This is the clandestine crime
syndicate: Baroque Works.

459
00:26:50.210 --> 00:26:53.590
That means... 1,800 plus 200, so...

460
00:26:53.590 --> 00:26:56.220
There are 2,000 underlings?!

461
00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:56.220
There's 2,000!

462
00:26:56.220 --> 00:26:58.300
Alright, I get it now!

463
00:26:58.300 --> 00:27:01.930
I just gotta kick this
Crocodile guy's butt, right?!

464
00:27:01.930 --> 00:27:04.140
Definitely in one ear
and out the other!

465
00:27:04.410 --> 00:27:09.110
If Baroque Works' last big job
is to take over this country...

466
00:27:09.110 --> 00:27:14.110
...the rest of those
officer agents will all...

467
00:27:14.110 --> 00:27:16.570
...gather in Alabasta.

468
00:27:17.490 --> 00:27:18.910
Yes.

469
00:27:18.910 --> 00:27:22.160
I see... Anyway, I just gotta kick
this Crocodile guy's butt–

470
00:27:22.160 --> 00:27:24.330
Cool it! We heard you the first time.

471
00:27:24.330 --> 00:27:25.080
Oh, yeah?

472
00:27:25.580 --> 00:27:28.380
Un, deux, ourrois!

473
00:27:25.620 --> 00:27:28.380
Little Garden,
The Island of Giants

474
00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:30.670
Un, deux, korrois!

475
00:27:31.800 --> 00:27:34.970
I-I'm sorry, Mr. 2 Bon Kurei!

476
00:27:35.760 --> 00:27:37.760
Nobody's clowning here!

477
00:27:37.760 --> 00:27:40.560
Who do you think I am?

478
00:27:42.060 --> 00:27:47.350
Mr. 2 Bon Kurei
Officer Agent, Baroque Works

479
00:27:42.430 --> 00:27:44.730
I'm Bon Kurei, a Baroque Works officer agent!

480
00:27:44.730 --> 00:27:47.190
Even swans fear me!

481
00:27:47.190 --> 00:27:49.770
Hey, you! Navigator!

482
00:27:50.150 --> 00:27:51.020
Y-Yes sir!

483
00:27:51.020 --> 00:27:55.530
Tell me again. What was
Zero baby's order?

484
00:27:55.530 --> 00:28:00.990
Kill Mr. 3 on the direct route
between Alabasta and Little Garden.

485
00:28:00.990 --> 00:28:04.870
So you do remember the mission.

486
00:28:06.210 --> 00:28:09.330
Direct route means
going in a straight line, right?

487
00:28:09.330 --> 00:28:14.630
That's why we traveled straight from
Alabasta to this Little Garden, right?!

488
00:28:14.630 --> 00:28:17.180
So tell me. What's going on?!

489
00:28:17.180 --> 00:28:22.260
We sailed straight from Alabasta to
Little Garden and never ran into Mr. 3!

490
00:28:22.260 --> 00:28:27.770
Doesn't that mean that
you guys missed Mr. 3's ship?!

491
00:28:28.190 --> 00:28:30.020
N-No...! Th-That can't be right...!

492
00:28:30.020 --> 00:28:33.020
Oh, so you're calling me stupid?

493
00:28:33.020 --> 00:28:34.280
No... Mr. 2–

494
00:28:34.280 --> 00:28:35.490
Shut up!

495
00:28:35.740 --> 00:28:43.240
Bon Kurei

496
00:28:36.240 --> 00:28:43.240
Anyway, operation "wipe out puny Mr. 3"
has to go off without a hitch!

497
00:28:43.240 --> 00:28:45.700
We can't afford to fail.

498
00:28:45.700 --> 00:28:49.710
If we do, Mr. 1 and his partner
will eliminate me.

499
00:28:50.710 --> 00:28:52.960
Do you understand?!

500
00:28:52.960 --> 00:28:58.680
If you don't want to feel my wrath,
locate Mr. 3 immediately.

501
00:28:58.680 --> 00:29:01.720
Super full speed! We're heading
to Alabasta on the Swanda!

502
00:29:01.720 --> 00:29:02.800
Now listen!

503
00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:05.560
Don't overlook even a dinghy!

504
00:29:05.560 --> 00:29:06.180
Yes, sir!

505
00:29:06.180 --> 00:29:08.850
– Mr. 2 Bon Kurei!
– Mr. 2 Bon Kurei!

506
00:29:10.560 --> 00:29:11.900
What?

507
00:29:11.900 --> 00:29:15.110
Pirates are attacking
towns in the kingdom?

508
00:29:15.110 --> 00:29:17.860
Don't they know this country
is under my protection?

509
00:29:17.860 --> 00:29:20.570
Who knows, Sir Crocodile?

510
00:29:21.070 --> 00:29:24.740
I guess a country in turmoil
is an appealing target for pirates.

511
00:29:28.040 --> 00:29:29.080
Heading out?

512
00:29:30.330 --> 00:29:34.460
Yes. I have a reputation to uphold.

513
00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:36.500
How sweet of you.

514
00:29:39.220 --> 00:29:40.840
Of course.

515
00:29:40.840 --> 00:29:44.890
The Seven Warlords of the Sea
are pirates who crush other pirates.

516
00:29:44.890 --> 00:29:47.270
We're heroes to the masses.
